DSP Usman Abdullahi, the spokesperson for the Taraba State Police Command, has confirmed the killing of a popular cattle merchant in Jalingo and the abduction of his wife and two sons on Wednesday. A source told DAILY POST that the businessman, Gidado-Hassan, a leading merchant in Jalingo, the state capital was attacked at his residence at Mallam Audu Village around 2am. The gunmen numbering about twelve, according to the sources, forced their way into the house of the businessman, led him and his family members to an unknown location, they shot him dead and left his lifeless body. He explained that the late Gidado Hassan was buried at Jika Da Dari main burial ground at about 9.30 am on Thursday. He said the abductors are yet to make any contact with the family for ransom.